<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   PRC's Yin Keshang, CPC Delegation Visit 14-22 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PRC's Yin Keshang, CPC Delegation Visit 14-22 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2405062594 Hanoi VNA in English 0604 GMT 24 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2405062594 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi May 24 -- A delegtion of the Communist Party 
of China (CPC) led by Yin Keshang member of the CPC Central 
Committee and secretary of the party committee of Qinghai 
Province, paid a visit to Vietnam from May 14-22 as guest of the 
Communist Party of Vietnam [CPV] Central Committee. 
  During the visit, the delegation paid a floral tribute to 
President Ho Chi Minh at his mausoleum and visited his home and 
office. 
  The Chinese guests were received by Pham The Duyet, member 
of 
CPV Central Committee and secretary of the Hanoi party 
committee. Mr. Duyet expressed his belief that the exchange of 
visits to explore the possibilities for cooperation will 
strengthen the friendship between the two peoples. 
  Mr. Yin Keshang welcomed the achievements recorded by the 
Vietnamese people in their renovation process and wished them 
bigger successes. 
  The Chinese party delegation also had working sessions with 
concerned offices, and party committees of Hanoi, Ho Chi Minh 
City and Provinces of Thanh Hoa, and Ben Tre, and visited a 
number of economic and cultural establishments. 

</TEXT>

