Daily Report 
<DATE1>  21 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Danish Trade Delegation Continues Visit in Hanoi </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Danish Trade Delegation Continues Visit in Hanoi </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Strategic Cooperation To Resume </H4>

<F P=102> BK2305135394 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
1430 GMT 21 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2305135394 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>
<F P=105>  Vietnamese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] With the goal of strengthening economic cooperation 
with Vietnam, a Danish Government delegation led by Minister for 
Development Cooperation Ms. Helle Aid Degn paid a working visit. 
Accompanying the Danish delegation was a large group of Danish 
businessmen. 
  During its stay in Vietnam, the Danish delegation was 
received by Deputy Prime Minister Phan Van Khai and held talks 
with Tran Thong Giao, deputy chairman of the State Planning 
Commission. Both sides noted that economic cooperation between 
the two countries is developing satisfactorily. 
  Denmark has resumed cooperation relations with Vietnam since 
1992 and has listed Vietnam as a preferential country in its 
program of overseas aid. It has granted Vietnam a nonrefundable 
aid of 83 million kroner or $14 million for the restoration and 
development of Denmark-funded projects in Vietnam such as the 
Hoang Thach cement factory, the La Nga sugar plant, and the 
Dalat water work. Both sides noted that Vietnam has effectively 
managed and exploited these projects. 
  Following the reopening of the Danish Embassy in Hanoi and 
the Consul General in Ho Chi Minh City, Denmark has informed 
Vietnam of a long-term strategic cooperation program under which 
the two countries will accelerate cooperation in preserving and 
processing of agricultural and sea products, developing cement 
production and distribution; and improving water supply, 
environmental protection, and care for women and children. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

