<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister Approves Association of Bankers </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Prime Minister Approves Association of Bankers </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2305130494 Hanoi VNA in English 1434 GMT 21 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2305130494 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA May 21 -- Prime Minister Vo Van Kiet has 
signed a decision permitting the establishment of the Vietnam 
Bankers Association (VBA). 
  VBA will be an NGO [Nongovernmental Organization] grouping 
on 
a voluntary basis all Vietnamese banking institutions, 
state-owned commercial banks, joint-stock banks and financial 
companies. 
  Apart from the state commercial banks, some 40 joint-stock 
banks and two financial companies are now operating in the 
country. 
  The new association will protect their rights within the 
legal framework. 
  It should also function to promote their modernisation and 
mediate any disputes between member banks. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

