<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister Establishes Thanh Hoa City </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Prime Minister Establishes Thanh Hoa City </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2305131994 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
1100 GMT 21 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2305131994 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>
<F P=105>  Vietnamese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Vo Van Kiet signed a decree dated 1 
May 1994 on the establishment of Thanh Hoa City in Thanh Hoa 
Province. The decree points out: The establishment of the city 
named Thanh Hoa will be based on the administrative units, area, 
population, and boundaries of the former Thanh Hoa provincial 
capital. 
  The Thanh Hoa city party committee, people's council, and 
people's committee convened a press conference on the afternoon 
of 20 May in Thanh Hoa to make public this decree of the prime 
minister of the government. The Thanh Hoa city party 
organization and people have invested six billion dong to build 
infrastructure, improve road conditions, and consolidate 
economic establishments and public utility projects to welcome a 
ceremony scheduled to take place in October this year to make 
public the prime minister's decree on the establishment of Thanh 
Hoa City. 

</TEXT>

