<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Phan Van Khai Attends Technology Conference </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Phan Van Khai Attends Technology Conference </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2305113494 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
2300 GMT 20 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2305113494 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>
<F P=105>  Vietnamese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 18-20 May, a conference on science, technology, 
and environment held in Hanoi for all provinces and cities 
directly subordinate to the central level. Nearly 200 delegates 
representing the central organs and departments for science, 
technology, and environment of 53 provinces and cities attended 
the conference. Deputy Prime Minister Phan Van Khai addressed 
the conference. He introduced issues relating to science, 
technology, and environment to the delegates. 
  The conference evaluated that the local activities on 
science, technology, and environment have contributed 
significantly to the national socioeconomic development. The 
role of science and technology have been confirmed in 
accelerating the national economic development. In 1993, all 
localities carried out 1,269 research projects, experimented 
with 170 production projects, applied 241 modern technologies, 
and imported 66 new technologies. 
  The conference outlined directions for the 1994 activities 
on 
science, technology, and evironment. The directions are to 
concentrate on regional advantages in setting up socioeconomic 
development goals in each province and city. 

</TEXT>

