<F P=100> NORTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   NEC To Set Up Joint Software Company in China </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    NEC To Set Up Joint Software Company in China </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2305102394 Tokyo KYODO in English 0954 GMT 23 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2305102394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, May 23 KYODO -- NEC Corp. said Monday [23 
May] it has signed an agreement with the Chinese Academy of 
Sciences [CAS] to jointly set up a computer software company in 
Beijing. NEC-CAS Software Laboratories Co. will be established 
June 15, with capital of about 150 million yen, NEC said. 
  NEC will hold 90 percent of the shares, while the rest will 
be owned by the Software Development Division of the Chinese 
Academy of Sciences -- the Institute of Software of the Academia 
Sinica. The company will develop software technology for 
personal computers and workstations to meet the growing market 
demand in China. The company projected sales in the first year 
will hit 60 million yen and reach 200 million yen by 1999, NEC 
officials said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

