<F P=100> Philippines </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further on Attempt To Hold Meeting on E. Timor </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further on Attempt To Hold Meeting on E. Timor </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Meeting With Indonesia Cancelled </H4>

<F P=102> BK2305111294 Quezon City GMA-7 Radio-Television Arts Network 
in Tagalog 0930 GMT 23 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2305111294 </F>
<F P=104>  Quezon City GMA-7 Radio-Television Arts Network 
in Tagalog 0930 GMT 23 May 94 </F>

<F P=105> Tagalog </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The crisis between the Philippines and Indonesia 
due to the upcoming conference on East Timor is still not over. 
A high-level meeting between Filipino and Indonesian officials 
was canceled earlier today. President Fidel Ramos was scheduled 
to meet Indonesian Industry Minister Tunki Ariwibowo and the 
Indonesian ambassador. However, the Indonesian Embassy revealed 
that Minister Ariwibowo is still in the United States, and the 
meeting was rescheduled. 
  Meanwhile, Malacanang [presidential office] officials 
admitted that the incident has something to do with the East 
Timor crisis. 

</TEXT>

