BFN 

<F P=106> [From NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN 24 May Morning Edition] </F>
  [Text] Tatsufumi Tsuboi, chief of the Cabinet Security 
Affairs Office, touched on the DPRK's (North Korea's) suspected 
development of nuclear arms at a Budget Committee session of the 
House of Representatives on 23 May. He disclosed that a joint 
council -- comprised of bureau chief-level officials at various 
ministries and agencies -- has been set up within the government 
and that it is now analyzing the situation concerning North 
Korea. He made the remarks in reply to questions by Shun Oide 
(of the Social Democratic Party of Japan). 

