<H3> <TI>   Kim Il-song Greets Jordan's King Husayn </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kim Il-song Greets Jordan's King Husayn </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2405112294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1010 GMT 24 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2405112294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 24 (KCNA) -- President Kim Il-song of 
the Democratic People's Republic of Korea today sent a message 
of greetings to his Majesty King Husayn the first of the 
Hashemite Kingdom of Jordan on the occasion of the 48th 
anniversary of the independence of Jordan. 
  President Kim Il-song in the message expressed the 
conviction 
that the friendly relations between the two countries would 
continue to develop in accordance with the desire and aspiration 
of their peoples, and wished the Hashemite Kingdom of Jordan 
prosperity. 

</TEXT>

