<H3> <TI>   Environment Minister To Attend UN Conference </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Environment Minister To Attend UN Conference </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2405004994 Seoul THE KOREA TIMES in English 24 May 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> SK2405004994 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul THE KOREA TIMES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Environment Minister Pak Yun-hun will leave for New 
York today to attend the three-day conference of the U.N. 
Commission on Sustainable Development (CSD) which begins 
Wednesday. 
  Pak, chief of the Korean delegation to the international 
forum, will speak on Korea's role and commitment in the 
environmental context and promise financial support for 
underdeveloped countries while calling for a transfer of clean 
technology from advanced countries. 
  The conference will be attended by 53 CSD member countries, 
the U.N. Environment Program, General Agreement on Tariffs and 
Trade (GATT) and other non-governmental organizations. 
  The participants will discuss implementing of Agenda 21 
adopted at the U.N. conference on environment and development in 
Rio de Janeiro in 1992. 
  The Korean delegation includes 11 officials from the 
Economic 
Planning Board, Foreign and Environment Ministries, and two non- 
governmental experts. 

</TEXT>

