<H3> <TI>   Early Visit to U.S. by Kakizawa Unlikely </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Early Visit to U.S. by Kakizawa Unlikely </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2505031594 Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database in Japanese 25 
May 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2505031594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN 25 May Morning Edition] </F>
  [Text] A top Foreign Ministry official commented on the 
evening of 24 May on the possibility of a visit by Foreign 
Minister Koji Kakizawa to the United States in view of the 
agreement to resume the Japan-U.S. economic framework talks. He 
indicated that there is very little possibility that the U.S. 
visit can materialize before the OECD executive ministerial 
committee meeting in early June. 
  This source also disclosed that Kakizawa told U.S. Trade 
Representative (USTR) Mickey Kantor during a telephone 
conversation on the same evening that an early trip to the 
United States would be unlikely, and that the two men agreed 
that Japan and the United States should consider holding a 
foreign ministerial meeting during the OECD meeting in Paris on 
7 and 8 June. 

</TEXT>

